Yes, it is absolutely possible to stay within a free tier on Google Cloud, especially for a project like yours!

Here is the breakdown of the costs and the advantages of moving from your local machine to the cloud.

💰 Is it free?
Yes, thanks to the Google Cloud Free Tier, you can run your OmniVision system at no cost for quite a long time if your usage stays low.

Cloud Run (Compute): The "Always Free" tier gives you 2 million requests per month and a significant amount of compute time (vCPU-seconds and GiB-seconds) for free.
Artifact Registry (Storage): You get 0.5 GB of storage for your container images for free each month.
$300 Credits: If you are a new user, you also get $300 in free credits to cover any usage beyond these limits for the first 90 days.
🚀 Advantages of Deploying to GCP vs. Local
While local development is great for coding, moving to the cloud offers several "unfair advantages" for your OmniVision platform:

Always-On Backend: Your authentication and user profile system will be available 24/7. Your users won't be disconnected the moment you close your laptop.
True Multi-User Testing: You can test the "Data Isolation" you built by having different people log in from different devices simultaneously.
App Hub Intelligence: Once on GCP, App Hub can automatically track your service's health, reliability, and even give you Gemini-powered recommendations to optimize your code or costs.
Eliminate "Works on My Machine": Deploying in a container to Cloud Run ensures that the environment is exactly the same every time, preventing bugs that happen only on your specific computer.
Easy Scaling: If you suddenly decide to add 100 cameras, Cloud Run will automatically scale up to handle the load and then scale back down to zero (and $0 cost) when no one is using it.
