That is a very common setup! Since you are using Windsurf and your frontend is already on GitHub, the easiest path to the cloud is to use a Git-based workflow.

Instead of manually uploading files, we will connect your code to Google Cloud so that whenever you "Commit" in Windsurf and "Push" to GitHub, Google Cloud will automatically build and update your service.

Here is the 3-step plan to do this directly from your Windsurf environment:

Step 1: Add a Dockerfile to your Backend
In Windsurf, create a new file named Dockerfile in your backend/ folder. This tells Google Cloud exactly how to run your Python API.

# Use an official Python runtime as a parent image
FROM python:3.11-slim

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the requirements file into the container
COPY requirements.txt .

